snippet.textDisplay:
Heads up 7 up, from what I remember, kids put their heads down, thumbs up, and then 7 students would go around and touch the thumbs of the other students, one each. The teacher says "Heads up, 7 up", (because one for each of the current taggers), and if you were tagged you'd stand up and guess who tagged you. If you were right you'd take their spot, if you were wrong they stay up... and the game went on and on... at least that's how we played it in my elementary school in Canada.

Also, I like Pepsi better than normal Coke, but Vanilla Coke is amazing, and Cherry Pepsi is pretty good too... also Barqs Root Beer is the best root beer.
